article.headline: UMKC 80, Chicago St 75
article.story: CHICAGO (AP) -- Dee Ayuba scored 22 points and grabbed nine rebounds to lead Missouri-Kansas City to a 80-75 victory over Chicago State on Wednesday night. After leading by as much as 11 points in the first half, Chicago State (1-13, 0-3 Mid-Continent Conference) took a 35-31 lead into the break. But the Kangaroos (5-7, 2-1) fought their way back in the second half, shooting 59.3 percent from the field to Chicago State's 48.3 percent. Brent Stephens had 17 points for UMKC, and Quinton Day scored 16. David Holston led the Cougars in scoring with 32, and Royce Parran added 11. Parran also had a game-high 10 assists.
